TEDx talks around the world have become a powerful platform for stimulataing conversation and sparking debate on a range of issues. On Friday evening, the sold-out inaugural edition of TEDx Lavington Women took place at the Braeburn Theatre, Gitanga road, Nairobi. Curated by Valentine Njoroge, the event aim is to amplify the voices of Kenyan women on a global platform through TEDx. Guests speakers included Supreme Court Lady Justice Njoki Ndungu, Amadiva founder Maureen Murunga, Safaricom consumer business director Sylvia Mulinge, investment professional Andia Chakava to name a few.